#
# Append-only log. scripts/mutants-gate.sh writes one row each time
# MUTANTS_GATE_OVERRIDE_REASON is set and the gate would otherwise block.
#
# Row format (pipe-separated):
#   <ISO-8601 UTC timestamp> | package=<crate> | exit=<cargo-mutants exit> |
#   cycle_end_tag=<tag> | actor=<GITHUB_ACTOR or $USER> | reason=<text>
#
# The label-based override path (PR titled / labelled
# `mutants-gate-override` that clears cycle_end_tag in releases.toml)
# does not write to this log; CODEOWNERS review on releases.toml is the
# audit trail for that path. This log only records the env-var escape
# hatch used in single CI runs where waiting on a CODEOWNERS-reviewed
# PR is not feasible.
#
# House rule: do not delete rows; rotate by archiving the entire file
# under docs/fuzzing/archive/ if it grows past a release cycle.
#
# --- begin entries ---
